Operations were suspended at the South Deep Mine pending a full risk assessment &amp; inspection. JOHANNESBURG Gold Fields Mine is investigating a tramming accident, which has claimed the life of one of its workers.Operations were suspended at the South Deep Mine on Thursday, pending a full risk assessment and inspection.This is the second mining fatality at the operation this year.Gold Field s Sven Lunsche says, It s a worst time in a mine s life to have an accident. We ve had two this year. So we obviously have to renew our efforts to address the underlying causes of this. 